<br>
Get a fast weapon.  who cares about the dmg, the more often your attacking the mob, the less he can ignore you.  most fast weaps are gonna be 1hs, that gives you a shield also.  Nice, now you have a bash button to go with your Taunt button.<br>
<br>
get fast casting low mana stuns and chain.  I usually use Cease and Desist, yes even on mobs that resist.  The aggro factor is still there even if the stun doesn't stick.<br>
<br>
in my experience where it was my duty to hold taunt, I wasn't worried about being the dmg dealer, that's a rogue or Nuker's job, my job is a mob-stopper.  I MA'd kael arena several times and only lost aggro once due to an uber shammy slow, and got it back in 2 rounds.  I was no way dmging the mob as much as others, but he couldn't ignore how fast I was hitting him, and the chain of stuns/bash/taunt I was throwing at him.  <br>
<br>
I'm never looked over to MA or split tank now.  Not because I have great AC or HP, that can come from buffs, but because I know how to plant a mobs Hate on myself and keep it.  Only classes able to take hate from me are Shammy, Chanter and SK if they really wanted too, but I'd get it right back. <p><br>Baron Lhorr Silvershoal</br>
