<br>
If I need aggro, I cast Holy Might and Stun.  Those two are almost always all I need to keep aggro through a fight.  I occaisionally throw a desist in the middle of the fight just for grins/insurance, but it's usually not necessary.<br>
<br>
I agree with Khalim.  Fast weapons are an EQ urban legend.  Aggro is all about damage and hate from spells.  It's not about hitting the mob fast, it's about hitting the mob for a pile of damage over a given amount of time.  You hit the mob 10 times for 200 points, I hit the mob 3 times for 400 points, I win.  It's that simple.  I have won aggro swinging a big 2 hander over warriors swinging fast 1 handers many times (without casting spells).<br>
<br>
Bottom line is that if your group is not practicing good aggro control, there is very little you can do.  If a melee wants to pound the taunt button, they will sometimes win aggro.  If a wizzie overnukes to start the fight, keeping aggro will be tough. <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=113786>Aelyn</a> 
